item.title: JWST Launches
item.description: James Webb Space Telescope Where is Webb Resources #UnfoldTheUniverse The successor to the Hubble Space Telescope, the James Webb Space Telescope launched at 2021-12-25T12:20Z from the ESA Launch Facility in French Guiana. It just has finished the starting part of the deployment sequence that spans 6 months, and it is cruising towards L2, 1.5 million km from the earth. Webb will see the lights emitted when the first stars were born over 13.
